# Split CGSD Approvals: Inspection vs. Asset Reports

## Goal

Right now, ALL `inventory_report` records with `approval_status = 'pending'` land in one shared **CGSD Approvals** page — whether they came from FAMCD's formal reports OR from FAMCD's ocular inspection submission.

The user wants them separated into **two distinct places**:

| Source | Currently goes to | Should go to |
|---|---|---|
| FAMCD ocular inspection → "Submit Report to CGSD" | `cgsd/approvals.tsx` ❌ | `cgsd/ocular-inspections.tsx` ✅ |
| FAMCD inventory reports → "Submit to CGSD" | `cgsd/approvals.tsx` ✅ | stays in `cgsd/approvals.tsx` ✅ |

---

## How to Tell Them Apart

When FAMCD submits from [ocular-inspections.tsx](file:///c:/Users/clare/Downloads/pafm-official-main/pafm-official-main/src/pages/famcd/ocular-inspections.tsx), it creates **both**:
- An `ocular_inspection` record
- An `inventory_report` record (linked via `inventory_request_id`)

When FAMCD submits from [inventory-reports.tsx](file:///c:/Users/clare/Downloads/pafm-official-main/pafm-official-main/src/pages/famcd/inventory-reports.tsx), it only creates/updates:
- An `inventory_report` record (NO `ocular_inspection` record for the same `inventory_request_id`)

So: **if an `ocular_inspection` record exists for the `inventory_request_id` → it's an inspection report, not a formal asset report.**

